system.description:
You have an almost supernatural connection with a loyal parrot or monkey. You can’t talk to it per se but it always acts as you wish it to.

When your parrot distracts your enemy during a brawl and you roll 12+ on Hack
and Slash, do +1d6 damage.

When your monkey picks a pocket or steals a small object, Roll+CHA

partial.value:
He gets the item but the GM also chooses one.

  • He draws attention to you and puts you in a spot.
  • He gets the wrong item, although it is not totally useless.
  • He gets chased and disappears for the rest of  the day.

success.value: He gets away with it, but hides for a while. You can get the object a bit later.

system.description:
Requires Master Navigator and Helmsman.

Your are qualified to be a ship’s captain.

Your crew takes +1 on Boarding rolls.
When you roll 10+ on hack and slash with a precise weapon, you disarm your opponent (If appropriate in the fiction)
When you hack and slash with a precise weapon, you take +1 armor forward.

When you interact with NPC’s your fearsome reputation works for you.

  • At 3rd to 5th level: Roll +3 instead of  +Cha.
  • At 6th level or higher: Roll +4 instead of  +Cha.
You can hold your breath for up to 5 minutes.

You are an expert at handling cannons.

Your ship does +1d4 cannon damage.

Your firearm does +1d4 damage.
Your ship takes +1 Maneuver rolls.
When you utter a grievous insult to an opponent intelligent enough to understand it, or his mother and the GM thinks your insult is funny, original or deserving of  recognition, Roll+CHA.

failure.value:
Your opponent makes the perfect comeback and takes +1d6 damage forward
against you.

partial.value: Take +1 and +1d4 damage forward to Hack and Slash against that opponent.

success.value: On 10+: Take +1 and +1d6 damage forward to Hack and Slash against that opponent.

system.description: When you are asked to present identification, cargo manifests, shipping documents, import documents or any other official stuff, Roll+CHA.

partial.value:
The GM chooses:

  • You have to promise to present it within a day or so to the proper authorities.
  • You have to pay a bribe.

success.value: You have some sort of paper you can flash and talk your way out of  it.

system.description: When you are inked with Kraken’s ink, and do not wear other armor, take +1 armor.
When you parley with someone who finds you attractive, take +1

Requires and replaces Gunner.

Your ship does +1d6 cannon damage.

Your firearm does +1d6 damage.

As long as you are at sea or can see the stars, you do not get lost.

You can predict weather accurately 48 hours in advance.

You can communicate with the soul of  the sea and the wind. When you do it to follow a trail left behind by passing ships or large or mystical sea creatures, roll+Wis.

partial.value:
You follow the ship or creature until there’s a significant change in its direction or
mode of  travel.

success.value:
You follow the ship or creature until there’s a significant change in its direction or
mode of  travel, and choose 1:

  • Gain a useful bit of  information about your quarry, the GM will tell you what.
  • Determine what caused the trail to end.

system.description:
When you go on a perilous sea journey, Roll+WIS.

When you Discern Realities while at sea, take +1.

You can predict the weather accurately 24 hours in advance.

success.value: You make excellent time and avoid foul weather.

system.description: You are an expert at handling black powder. You can make black powder out of  the raw material (charcoal, saltpetre and sulphur) and can use it to blow stuff  up. You do not have to Defy Danger in order to use black powder.
When you use a musket at long range to volley, take +1
When you encounter a new culture with a foreign tongue, Roll+INT.
When you find the treasure Roll+Wis

partial.value: The treasure is 20% more than it would have been.

success.value: The treasure is 50% more than it would have been.

system.description: When you Discern Realities while reading a map, you may ask “Where is the treasure?”

partial.value: The answer is a bit more vague and cryptic.

success.value: The answer is more or less straight.

items.name: Yo Ho Ho! And a Bottle of Rum

system.description:
When you fight while under the influence of rum,

  • Take +1 armor.
  • Take +1 to all Cha rolls.
  • Take  -1 to all Wis rolls.

When you win a tavern brawl while inebriated, take +1 to the Carouse move.

system.tagsString: +3 damage, two-handed, near, loud, 1 piercing, messy, forceful, reload

system.description: When you enter a port or town you have been before (your call) Roll+CHA.

failure.value: They make life complicated for you and your party.

partial.value: They are willing to help at a price.

success.value: You know someone who is willing to help you.

system.description: Whatever you do with ropes, it is always successful if the fiction allows it.
When you defy danger in water, take +1.
When you perform a feat of  acrobatics using the environment to your advantage. Describe what you do and roll+Dex

partial.value:
You sort of succeed but (GM chooses)

  • You open yourself to attack
  • You drop something important
  • You take -1 forward as you land where you did not plan to.

success.value: You execute the maneuvre perfectly as planned and take 1+ forward.

system.description: When you Hack and Slash with precise weapon in one hand and a pistol in the other, add your pistol's damage to your melee damage as long as you still have loaded pistols.
